** Dinobot growled and watched the damage he had inflicted upon Sixshot, 
finding that the bot had already been weakened before he had arrived.
All the same, the sooner he took him out the sooner he could move onto the 
next bot.
But then his optics sharpen theit focus as he watches Sixshot fire off two 
bolts, four blasts coming towards him from both.
Jumping back a few feet as he sent four charges towards him, but realizing 
too late that he hadn't backed off far enough.
The charges hit the ground while one other hit right in front of him, the 
explosion from the impace throwing him back a few feet.
Dinobot landed hard with a grunt, dirt pattering against his chest as he lay 
there for a few second before he suddenly recognized a sound.
A charge!
By the sound it was coming in the wrong direction then Sixshot.
He quickly got to his feet as the sound got closer, scanning the area for 
the sender of the charge and finally spotting him as the charge exploded 
harmlessly a few meters away.
Arese!
Dinobot growled.*
